				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">IIRC, the OneBus VT Famiclones were the only ones that supported the higher bitdepth, and their documents explain how they do things...<br /><br />On the NES, during rendering, every pixel is either a setup cycle or a read cycle; IIRC on the OneBus famiclone, every three pixels are always a CPU bus cycle and two fetches for the PPU, for an aggregate PPU data transfer rate of 3.6MB/s instead of 2.7MB/s. Additionally I don't think the attribute zones work the same way, and sprites might always be 2bpp.<br /><br />Since the onebus famiclones in onebus mode are fundamentally incompatible with ordinary NES games, there's no real need to retain a compatible fetch sequence.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

